				\begin{document}$$ {Im}\bar{\text{3}} $$\end{document}), as a filled variant. The chemical formula of these compounds can be described as EyT4X12, where T is a transition element of the VIII group in 8c (¼, ¼, ¼); the electropositive element (E) occupies the icosahedral hole in 2a (0, 0, 0) which can be filled by a number of electropositive elements such as Ca, Sr, Ba, Tl, lanthanides and actinides, or under special conditions by Y, Hf, Pb and Sn (high pressure or multilayer precursor methods) and by K and Na (in nanowire state); X is a pnicogen or one of the IVA-VIA elements in the 24 g site (0, y, z). Some elements like Sn were found to be able to occupy the 24 g site (Co4Sb12−ySny, CoSn6Te6, La1−xCo4Sb12−ySny, Yb1−xCo4Sb12−ySny, Tl1−xCo4Sb12−ySny) as well as the 2a site (SnyNi4Sb12−xSnx). The icosahedral cage in the skutterudite structure may be filled also by electronegative fillers such as I and Br.
